<Page x:Class="AsynAwaitExamples.Steps.Step20_AsyncLinq"
      xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
      xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
      xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:AsynAwaitExamples.ViewModels"
      Title="Step 20 - Async LINQ">
    <Page.DataContext>
        <vm:Step20ViewModel/>
    </Page.DataContext>
    <ScrollViewer VerticalScrollBarVisibility="Auto">
        <StackPanel Margin="10">
            <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource HeaderStyle}" 
                       Text="Step 20: Async LINQ Operations"/>

            <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource ExplanationStyle}" xml:space="preserve">ASYNC LINQ: Filtering, transforming, and collecting async streams.

Standard LINQ (Where, Select, Take) works on IEnumerable&lt;T&gt;, not
IAsyncEnumerable&lt;T&gt;. You can write async LINQ manually using
"await foreach" + "yield return", or use the System.Linq.Async NuGet package.

This step shows the manual approach. It teaches the underlying pattern.
Each operation processes items lazily, one at a time, as they arrive.

KEY OPERATIONS:
- WhereAsync: filter items from an async stream.
- SelectAsync / SelectAwaitAsync: transform items (sync or async transform).
- TakeAsync: yield at most N items, then stop.
- ToListAsync: collect all items into a List (breaks lazy evaluation).</TextBlock>

            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="[1] Filter: async Where (even numbers only)"
                    Command="{Binding FilterDemoCommand}"/>
            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="[2] Transform: async Select (product lookup)"
                    Command="{Binding TransformDemoCommand}"/>
            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="[3] Pipeline: Where -> Select -> Take"
                    Command="{Binding PipelineDemoCommand}"/>
            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="[4] Collect: ToListAsync"
                    Command="{Binding CollectDemoCommand}"/>

            <TextBox Style="{StaticResource OutputStyle}" Height="280"
                     Text="{Binding OutputText, Mode=OneWay}"/>
        </StackPanel>
    </ScrollViewer>
</Page>
